# 📌 3. RIP (Routing Information Protocol)

## 🔹 Concept (Say this)

> “RIP is a distance-vector routing protocol that uses hop count as a metric. Maximum hop count is 15.”

---

## 🔹 How it Works

* Routers share routing tables every **30 seconds**
* Chooses path with **least hops**

---

## 🔧 RIP Configuration (On ALL routers)

```bash id="1nq2xl"
configure terminal
router rip
version 2
no auto-summary
network 192.168.1.0
network 192.168.2.0
network 192.168.3.0
network 10.0.0.0
```

👉 Each router should include:

* Its LAN network
* WAN network

