# 📌 4. OSPF (Open Shortest Path First)

## 🔹 Concept (Say this)

> “OSPF is a link-state routing protocol that uses cost (bandwidth) and calculates shortest path using Dijkstra algorithm.”

---

## 🔹 How it Works

* Routers exchange **link-state information**
* Builds full network map
* Faster and more efficient than RIP

---

## 🔧 OSPF Configuration (On ALL routers)

```bash id="b0z3ux"
configure terminal
router ospf 1
network 192.168.1.0 0.0.0.255 area 0
network 192.168.2.0 0.0.0.255 area 0
network 192.168.3.0 0.0.0.255 area 0
network 10.0.0.0 0.0.0.255 area 0
```

---

